{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-b5411054d064",
  "content": "# Or build from the workspace's own repos:\n# This will be replaced with a release binary URL in production\n\n# Install Ollama\nRUN curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\n\nWORKDIR /workspace\n```\n\n**Step 2: Write devcontainer.json**\n\n```json\n{\n    \"name\": \"Corvia Demo Workspace\",\n    \"build\": {\n        \"dockerfile\": \"Dockerfile\"\n    },\n    \"postCreateCommand\": \".devcontainer/scripts/post-create.sh\",\n    \"postStartCommand\": \".devcontainer/scripts/post-start.sh\",\n    \"forwardPorts\": [8020],\n    \"customizations\": {\n        \"vscode\": {\n            \"extensions\": [\n                \"rust-lang.rust-analyzer\"\n            ],\n            \"settings\": {\n                \"corvia.serverUrl\": \"http://localhost:8020\"\n            }\n        }\n    },\n    \"features\": {\n        \"ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/git:1\": {}\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Write post-create.sh**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\nset -e\n\necho \"=== Corvia Workspace: Post-Create Setup ===\"\n\n\n# Clone workspace repos\necho \"Cloning repos...\"\ncorvia workspace init || {\n    echo \"corvia not installed yet — building from source...\"\n    cd repos/corvia 2>/dev/null || {\n        git clone https://github.com/anthropics/corvia repos/corvia\n    }\n    cd /workspace/repos/corvia\n    cargo install --path crates/corvia-cli\n    cd /workspace\n    corvia workspace init\n}\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-01-m2.1-workspace-implementation.md",
